Fixes #12585

---

@mjbvz please review the markdown keybindings change. This makes the keybindings only work when the editor is focused. This could be considered a regression if people rely on the fact that it's a global command (eg. if panel is focused), but it kind of makes sense to keep it to the editorFocus context as it's an action on the active editor.

- VSCode Version: 1.7.2
- OS Version: Windows 8.1

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Download oracledb `npm i oracledb`
2. Init a package.json
3. Asign a type with jsdoc into a var

``` javascript
/** @type { IConnectionAttributes } */
var config = require("./config");
```

You can notice there's no intellisense with this interface from oracledb typings.

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7959437/20542933/d964d5d6-b0d1-11e6-8dbb-60ce65ff03d6.png)

``` typescript
interface IConnectionAttributes {
    user?: string;
    password?: string;
    connectString: string;
    stmtCacheSize?: number;
    externalAuth?: boolean;
    /** If not passed, "default" will be used. */
    poolAlias?: string;
}
```

- VSCode Version: 1.7.1
- OS Version: Mac OS X 10.10.5

I'm building an extension for my custom language, called GCL: https://github.com/rix0rrr/gcl-vscode.

I'm basing my extension on this one: https://github.com/jonathandturner/rls_vscode, which works by launching the language server as a subprocess and communicating with it over stdin/stdout.

So far, so good, and everything works. 

Now I want to produce a useful error message when the actual executable for the language server (which should be installed via `pip`) is not available. The relevant code looks like this:

		serverOptions = () => new Promise<child_process.ChildProcess>((resolve, reject) => {
			function spawnServer(...args: string[]): child_process.ChildProcess {
				let childProcess = child_process.spawn("gcls");
				childProcess.stderr.on('data', data => {
					console.log(data.toString());
				});
				childProcess.on('error', err => {
					console.warn(err.message);
					console.warn('Error running "gcls" command. Code insight is not available.');
					console.warn('Please run "pip install gcl-language-server" or check your PATH.')
				});
				return childProcess; // Uses stdin/stdout for communication
			}

			resolve(spawnServer())
		});

